  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Do not open fuel tanks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Police Headquarters has directed the police to reject the requests made by the public to open the fuel tanks at petrol stations if they run out of fuel.",
        "Police spokesman Nihal Taltuwa said such actions could only be taken by the management and staff of the petrol station or by representatives appointed by the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation.",
        "He noted that the opening of fuel tanks should be done under safety measures and that such measures could be catastrophic.",
        "A police spokesman said police had been instructed to videotape those who behaved indecently at gas stations.",
        "Meanwhile, 675 suspects have so far been arrested on charges of illegally storing and selling fuel in a nationwide police raid based on various information available that some people were illegally storing fuel.",
        "He added that 21,636 liters of petrol, 33,462 liters of diesel and 11,100 liters of kerosene were seized during the raid."
      ],
